= "a solidarity network and community of practice where civic innovators, stewards, and patrons collaborate to address the complex challenges of our time. Our focus is on fostering regenerative, decentralized solutions". [https://wiki.opencivics.co/About+OpenCivics/About+Wiki]


=Description=

The [https://wiki.opencivics.co/About+OpenCivics/About+Wiki OpenCivics Network Wiki] "Supports place-based organizers and civic innovators by providing open methodologies, protocol libraries, and participatory governance tools.

Knowledge & Ontologies: Content is structured around an open protocols library, using a hierarchical knowledge system:

● Patterns describe broad solution domains (e.g. bioregional mapping).
● Protocols provide step-by-step instructions for specic actions (e.g. citizen science).
● Playbooks bundle protocols into applied models (e.g. participatory mapping workshop +
eco-credit creation process)."

(https://www.r3-0.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Bioregional-Knowledge-Commons-A-Meta-Perspective.pdf?)

